    • 程序包 org.kelvinizer.game.gamewindow

      • 类 org.kelvinizer.game.gamewindow.Chart

        class Chart extends AnimatablePanel implements Serializable

        • 序列化字段

          • cb
            ChartButtons cb
            An instance of the ChartButtons class, responsible for managing the buttons and their interactions in the chart UI, such as restart or exit buttons.
          • ct
            ChartText ct
            An instance of the ChartText class, responsible for handling the text display in the chart, such as the song title, artist, and other text elements.
          • goBack
            boolean goBack
            Flag indicating whether the user should go back to the previous screen.
          • inputStream
            AudioInputStream inputStream
            The AudioInputStream used to read audio data for the song associated with the chart.
          • isDown
            boolean[] isDown
            Array of booleans representing the state of the keys (pressed or not) corresponding to each lane. Each element tracks whether the key for a specific lane is currently pressed (true) or not (false).
          • isPaused
            boolean isPaused
            Flag indicating whether the game is currently paused.
          • keyboardActivation
            int[] keyboardActivation
            Array of key codes representing the keyboard keys assigned to activate each lane. Corresponds to specific keys (A, S, D, F, J, K, L, etc.) for user input.
          • lanes
            Lane[] lanes
            An array of Lane objects representing the 16 different lanes in the game. Each lane corresponds to a specific area where notes are displayed and interactable.
          • music
            Clip music
            The Clip object used to play the audio for the song. It interfaces with the AudioInputStream to produce sound during the gameplay.
          • progressBar
            CRect progressBar
            A CRect object representing the progress bar in the chart, which visually indicates the current progress in the song. It is positioned at the top of the screen.
          • signal
            int[] signal
            Array of integers representing the activation signals for each lane. A signal value of 1 indicates that the key for the lane is pressed, and -1 indicates it is released.
          • STATIC_TIMER
            double STATIC_TIMER
            A static timer that tracks the elapsed time in the chart. It is used for timing-related functions.
          • timePoint
            double timePoint
            The time point of the game, typically used to track the position in the music or game timeline.
